paragraph.text:
assisting
				developing countries to provide all children with a quality basic education,
				including through strengthening host countries’ educational systems;

subparagraph.text:
coordination among
				governments, multilateral organizations, private sector, and civil
				society;

mutual
				accountability between donors and recipients for achieving measurable results
				in access and quality;

the Committee
			 on Appropriations and the Committee on Foreign Relations of the Senate;
			 and

clause.text:
build the
				institutional capacity of a country to manage basic education systems and
				measure results;

subparagraph.text:
may be developed
				in accordance with the provisions of the Global Partnership for Education;
				and

seek to build
				capacity within developing countries for basic education programs in order to
				make progress toward the goal of achieving sustainable development;

target the
				activities of the United States to leverage contributions from other bilateral
				donors to provide quality universal basic education;

to promote the
				development and effective use of systems for monitoring and evaluating
				student-learning outcomes;

to eliminate fees
				for educational services, including fees for tuition, uniforms, and materials
				as part of a comprehensive education financing plan;

to identify and
				replicate successful interventions that improve access to and quality of
				education;

to build systems
				to ensure continuing information collection, monitoring, and evaluation of
				education services and financing;

to promote
				programs that teach civic education, critical thinking, leadership and life
				skills;

clause.text:
promoting efforts
				to establish and enforce strong laws and policies against school-related
				violence;

supporting
				efforts to train all teachers and school administrators on school-related
				violence;

working to
				ensure the safety of students during their travel to and from schools and on
				school grounds;

improving school
				infrastructure to increase safety, such as by constructing separate latrines
				for boys and girls;

carrying out
				programs for school and community participation on the unacceptability of
				violence;

providing
				counseling and support systems for students affected by school-related
				violence;

subparagraph.text:
to work with
				communities to achieve equity in schools and address gender norms to build
				support for girls’ education;

to promote the
				creation of out-of-school programs and flexible-hour schooling in areas in
				which security prevents students from attending regular schools;

to provide
				assistance for temporary and permanent education facility construction and
				minor rehabilitation and equipping of educational structures;

to provide
				essential educational services and materials that assist in building systems to
				support, train, and provide professional development for educators;

to build national
				capacity to coordinate and manage education in emergency response and
				recovery;
